des:
Amazon Alexa and the FriendSync Lamp work together to help you control your lamp nice and easy.
You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light. 
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust your lamp - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show. 
After connecting Alexa to your FriendSync Lamp in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "FriendSync Lamp" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register an account in our "FriendSync Lamp" app;
(3). You need to have your Friendship lamp in hand;
(4). Configure the device in our "FriendSync Lamp" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "FriendSync Lamp" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "FriendSync Lamp" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "FriendSync Lamp", and you'll be navigated to the login page;
(9). Input your FriendSync Lamp account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on lamp"
“Alexa, turn off lamp"
“Alexa, dim lamp"
“Alexa, brighten lamp"
“Alexa, set the lamp to 20 percent"
“Alexa, set lamp to Blue"
